Next, I swapped the bar2-bar1 columns back and joined this relation with itself only when both bars are equal. This removed any unintentional duplicates. 
Finally, I diff-ed the duplicate-free relation from the original relation of all bar1-bar2 combinations, and projected bar2 and bar1 to return the correct order.

SELECT bar2, bar1
FROM (
  SELECT bar AS bar1, beer, name AS bar2
  FROM Serves, Bar
  EXCEPT
  SELECT name AS bar1, beer, bar AS bar2
  FROM Serves, bar
) as t1
EXCEPT
-- subtract off: second in pair does not serve some beer that the first does
SELECT bar1, bar2
FROM (
  SELECT bar AS bar1, beer, name AS bar2
  FROM Serves, Bar
  EXCEPT
  SELECT name AS bar1, beer, bar AS bar2
  FROM Serves, Bar
) as t2;

column1:
(Select b1.name, b2.name
From Bar as b1, Bar as b2
where b1.name<>b2.name

except

Select b3.name, b4.name
From Serves as s1, Serves as s2, Bar as b3, Bar as b4
Where  b3.name=s1.bar and b4.name=s2.bar and s1.beer not in (select beer from Serves where bar=s2.bar))

intersect 

(Select distinct b3.name, b4.name
From Serves as s1, Serves as s2, Bar as b3, Bar as b4
Where  b3.name=s1.bar and b4.name=s2.bar and (s1.beer not in (select beer from Serves where bar=s2.bar) or s2.beer not in (select beer from Serves where bar=s1.bar)));

SELECT s6.bar1 AS bar1, s6.bar2 AS bar2
FROM (
	SELECT *
	FROM (
		SELECT bar AS bar1
		FROM serves
	) AS s1, 
	(
		SELECT bar AS bar2
		FROM serves
	) AS s2
	WHERE NOT s1.bar1 = s2.bar2

	EXCEPT

	(SELECT DISTINCT s5.bar1, s5.bar2
	FROM (
	SELECT DISTINCT s1.bar1, s1.beer, s2.bar2
	FROM (
		SELECT bar AS bar1, beer
		FROM serves
	) AS s1, 
	(
		SELECT bar AS bar2
		FROM serves
	) AS s2
	WHERE NOT s1.bar1 = s2.bar2

	EXCEPT

	SELECT DISTINCT s3.bar, s3.beer, s4.bar
	FROM (
		SELECT *
		FROM serves
	) AS s3,
	(
		SELECT *
		FROM serves
	) AS s4
	WHERE s3.beer = s4.beer AND NOT s3.bar = s4.bar
	) AS s5) 
) AS s6

EXCEPT

SELECT s6.bar2 AS bar1, s6.bar1 AS bar2
FROM (
	SELECT *
	FROM (
		SELECT bar AS bar1
		FROM serves
	) AS s1, 
	(
		SELECT bar AS bar2
		FROM serves
	) AS s2
	WHERE NOT s1.bar1 = s2.bar2

	EXCEPT

	(SELECT DISTINCT s5.bar1, s5.bar2
	FROM (
	SELECT DISTINCT s1.bar1, s1.beer, s2.bar2
	FROM (
		SELECT bar AS bar1, beer
		FROM serves
	) AS s1, 
	(
		SELECT bar AS bar2
		FROM serves
	) AS s2
	WHERE NOT s1.bar1 = s2.bar2

	EXCEPT

	SELECT DISTINCT s3.bar, s3.beer, s4.bar
	FROM (
		SELECT *
		FROM serves
	) AS s3,
	(
		SELECT *
		FROM serves
	) AS s4
	WHERE s3.beer = s4.beer AND NOT s3.bar = s4.bar
	) AS s5) 
) AS s6
;

SELECT DISTINCT S1.bar AS bar1, S2.bar AS bar2 FROM Serves S1, Serves S2 WHERE NOT S1.bar = S2.bar
EXCEPT
(SELECT DISTINCT S1.bar AS bar1, NotServes.bar AS bar2 
 FROM Serves AS S1, 
 (SELECT DISTINCT bar, name AS beer FROM Serves, Beer EXCEPT SELECT bar, beer FROM Serves) AS NotServes 
 WHERE (NOT S1.bar = NotServes.bar AND S1.beer = NotServes.beer)) 
 UNION 
 SELECT S1.bar AS bar1, S2.bar AS bar2 
 FROM Serves AS S1, Serves AS S2
 WHERE NOT EXISTS (SELECT beer FROM Serves WHERE (beer NOT IN (SELECT s3.beer FROM Serves s3, Serves s4 WHERE NOT s3.bar = S4.bar AND s3.beer = S4.beer)));

WITH TMP1 (bar1, beer1, price1, bar2, beer2, price2) AS 
(SELECT serves1.bar AS bar1, serves1.beer AS beer1, serves1.price AS price1, serves2.bar AS bar2, serves2.beer AS beer2, serves2.price AS price2 
FROM serves AS serves1 CROSS JOIN serves AS serves2),

TMP2 (bar1,bar2,beer1) AS
(SELECT bar1,bar2,beer1
FROM TMP1),

TMP3 (bar1,bar2,beer2) AS
(SELECT bar1,bar2,beer2
FROM TMP1),

TMP4 (bar1,bar2,beer1) AS
(SELECT * 
FROM TMP2
EXCEPT 
SELECT * 
FROM TMP3)

SELECT bar2,bar1 
FROM TMP4
EXCEPT
SELECT bar1,bar2 
FROM TMP4;

select sc1.bar, sc2.bar
from (select distinct bar, count(beer) from serves group by bar) as sc1, (select distinct bar, count(beer) from serves group by bar) as sc2
where sc1.count < sc2.count and sc1.bar <> sc2.bar
except
(select sc1.bar, sc2.bar
from (select distinct bar, count(beer) from serves group by bar) as sc1, (select distinct bar, count(beer) from serves group by bar) as sc2
where sc1.count < sc2.count and sc1.bar <> sc2.bar
intersect
select distinct s.bar, ns.bar
from 
	(
		(select distinct bar, beer
		 from (select distinct bar from serves) as one, (select distinct beer from serves) as two)
		except
		(select distinct bar, beer from serves)
	) as ns, (select distinct bar, beer from serves) as s
where ns.beer = s.beer and ns.bar <> s.bar);

with sameBeers(bar1, bar2) as
(select b1.name as bar1, b2.name as bar2 from bar as b1, bar as b2 where not exists
  ((select beer from serves as s1 where s1.bar = b1.name) except
      (select beer from serves as s2 where s2.bar = b2.name)) and not exists

      ((select beer from serves as s1 where s1.bar = b2.name) except
          (select beer from serves as s2 where s2.bar = b1.name)) and b1.name <> b2.name),
   oneServesMore(bar1, bar2) as (select b1.name as bar1, b2.name as bar2 from bar as b1, bar as b2 where exists
  ((select beer from serves as s1 where s1.bar = b1.name) except
      (select beer from serves as s2 where s2.bar = b2.name)))
select b3.name as bar1, b4.name as bar2 from bar as b3, bar as b4 where b3.name <> b4.name
except ((select * from oneServesMore) union (select * from sameBeers));

-- Find all (bar1, bar2) pairs where the set of beer served at bar1 is a proper subset of those served at
-- bar2; i.e., bar2 serves every beer that bar1 serves and plus some more.

-- (\project_{bar_1, bar_2}
-- ((\rename_{bar_1,beer_1,price_1} serves) \join_{bar_1<>bar_2}
-- (\rename_{bar_2,beer_2,price_2} serves)))
-- \diff
-- (\project_{bar_1,bar_2}
-- 	(\rename_{bar_1,beer,bar_2} ( // bar_2 serves a beer that bar_1 doesn't
-- 		(\project_{bar_1,beer,bar_2} (\rename_{bar_1,beer,bar_2}
-- 		(\project_{bar,beer,name} (serves \cross bar))))
-- 		\diff
-- 		(\project_{bar_1,beer,bar_2} (\rename_{bar_2,beer,bar_1}
-- 		(\project_{bar,beer,name} (serves \cross bar)))))));

(select s1.bar, s2.bar from serves as s1
join serves as s2
on s1.bar<>s2.bar)
except
(select distinct bar, name from
  ((select serves.bar, beer, bar.name
  from serves
  cross join bar)
  except
  (select bar.name, beer, serves.bar
  from serves
  cross join bar)) as t);

(


(SELECT diff1.bar2, diff1.bar1 FROM 
((SELECT pair.bar AS bar1, pair.beer AS beer, pair.name AS bar2
FROM (SELECT serves.bar, serves.beer, x.name FROM serves CROSS JOIN (SELECT name FROM bar) AS x) AS pair)

EXCEPT ALL

(SELECT pair.name AS bar1, pair.beer AS beer, pair.bar AS bar2
FROM (SELECT serves.bar, serves.beer, x.name FROM serves CROSS JOIN (SELECT name FROM bar) AS x) AS pair)
) AS diff1)


EXCEPT ALL



(SELECT bar1, bar2 FROM 

(SELECT diff1.bar2, diff1.bar1 FROM 
((SELECT pair.bar AS bar1, pair.beer AS beer, pair.name AS bar2
FROM (SELECT serves.bar, serves.beer, x.name FROM serves CROSS JOIN (SELECT name FROM bar) AS x) AS pair)

EXCEPT ALL

(SELECT pair.name AS bar1, pair.beer AS beer, pair.bar AS bar2
FROM (SELECT serves.bar, serves.beer, x.name FROM serves CROSS JOIN (SELECT name FROM bar) AS x) AS pair)
) AS diff1) AS revdiff, 


(SELECT diff2.bar3, diff2.bar4 FROM

(SELECT helper.bar1 AS bar3, helper.beer AS beer, helper.bar2 AS bar4 FROM
((SELECT pair.bar AS bar1, pair.beer AS beer, pair.name AS bar2
FROM (SELECT serves.bar, serves.beer, x.name FROM serves CROSS JOIN (SELECT name FROM bar) AS x) AS pair)

EXCEPT ALL

(SELECT pair.name AS bar1, pair.beer AS beer, pair.bar AS bar2
FROM (SELECT serves.bar, serves.beer, x.name FROM serves CROSS JOIN (SELECT name FROM bar) AS x) AS pair)) AS helper) AS diff2) AS diff

WHERE

bar1= bar4 and bar3=bar2)) AS res;

SELECT one.abar, two.bbar FROM
	((SELECT bar AS abar, beer AS abeer FROM serves) AS one 
		JOIN
	(SELECT bar AS bbar, beer AS bbeer FROM serves) AS two 
		ON one.abar != two.bbar)

EXCEPT 

SELECT three.abar, three.bbar FROM (
	(SELECT one.abar, two.bbar, one.beer FROM
			((SELECT bar AS abar, beer FROM serves) AS one 
				CROSS JOIN
			(SELECT name AS bbar FROM bar) AS two))
	EXCEPT

	(SELECT two.abar, one.bbar, one.beer FROM 
			((SELECT bar AS bbar, beer FROM serves) AS one 
				CROSS JOIN
			(SELECT name AS abar FROM bar) AS two)) ) AS three;

from serves group by bar) as bar1, (select bar, array_agg(beer) from

---- Collaborated with other students in TA office hours


(SELECT main.name, main.bar FROM

  (
    (SELECT Serves.bar, Serves.beer, Bar.name FROM Serves CROSS JOIN Bar)
    EXCEPT
    (SELECT Bar.name, Serves.beer, Serves.bar FROM Serves CROSS JOIN Bar)
  )

AS main)


EXCEPT

(SELECT diff.bar, diff.name FROM

  (
    (SELECT Serves.bar, Serves.beer, Bar.name FROM Serves CROSS JOIN Bar)
    EXCEPT
    (SELECT Bar.name, Serves.beer, Serves.bar FROM Serves CROSS JOIN Bar)
  )

  AS diff);

SELECT s1.bar as bar1, s2.bar as bar2 FROM serves s1 INNER JOIN serves s2 ON s1.bar <> s2.bar
EXCEPT
SELECT A.bar1 as bar1, A.bar2 as bar2 FROM (

	SELECT s1.bar as bar1, s2.bar as bar2, s1.beer as beer FROM serves s1 INNER JOIN serves s2 ON s1.bar <> s2.bar
	EXCEPT
	SELECT s1.bar as bar1, s2.bar as bar2, s2.beer as beer FROM serves s1 INNER JOIN serves s2 ON s1.bar <> s2.bar
) as A

EXCEPT
/*need to remove any pairs where (bar1, bar2) AND (bar2, bar1) exist.*/
(
SELECT result.bar2 as bar1, result.bar1 as bar2 FROM (
	SELECT s1.bar as bar1, s2.bar as bar2 FROM serves s1 INNER JOIN serves s2 ON s1.bar <> s2.bar
	EXCEPT
	SELECT B.bar1 as bar1, B.bar2 as bar2 FROM (

		SELECT s1.bar as bar1, s2.bar as bar2, s1.beer as beer FROM serves s1 INNER JOIN serves s2 ON s1.bar <> s2.bar
		EXCEPT
		SELECT s1.bar as bar1, s2.bar as bar2, s2.beer as beer FROM serves s1 INNER JOIN serves s2 ON s1.bar <> s2.bar
	) as B
) as result

SELECT
bar2,
bar1
FROM
(SELECT bar2 as bar1, beer, bar1 as bar2 FROM
(SELECT bar AS bar1, beer, name AS bar2 FROM (SELECT bar, beer FROM SERVES) AS Serves1 CROSS JOIN (SELECT name FROM Bar) AS bar1) AS E1
-- bar1 serves beer it is paired with each bar2 = e1
EXCEPT
(SELECT bar AS bar2, beer, name AS bar1 FROM (SELECT bar, beer FROM SERVES) AS Serves1 CROSS JOIN (SELECT name FROM Bar) AS bar1)) AS E2
-- bar2 doesn't serve beer but bar1 does = e2
EXCEPT
(SELECT bar1, bar2 FROM
(SELECT bar2 as bar1, beer, bar1 as bar2 FROM
(SELECT bar AS bar1, beer, name AS bar2 FROM (SELECT bar, beer FROM SERVES) AS Serves1 CROSS JOIN (SELECT name FROM Bar) AS bar1) AS E1
EXCEPT
(SELECT bar AS bar2, beer, name AS bar1 FROM (SELECT bar, beer FROM SERVES) AS Serves1 CROSS JOIN (SELECT name FROM Bar) AS bar1)) AS E2
)
--(bar1,bar2) is in e2 but bar2 does not serve every beer bar1 serves
--the answer will come out as (bar2,bar1) from e2 to make sure that bar2 serves some that bar1 doesnt
;

column1:
(select distinct bar1, bar2
from 
((select distinct b1.name AS bar1, b2.name AS bar2, s1.beer AS beer
from bar AS b1, bar AS b2, serves as s1
where b1.name <> b2.name
and b2.name = s1.bar
)
EXCEPT
(select distinct b1.name AS bar1, b2.name AS bar2, s1.beer AS beer
from bar AS b1, bar AS b2, serves as s1
where b1.name <> b2.name
and b1.name = s1.bar)) AS sub)
EXCEPT 
(select distinct bar2, bar1
from 
((select distinct b1.name AS bar1, b2.name AS bar2, s1.beer AS beer
from bar AS b1, bar AS b2, serves as s1
where b1.name <> b2.name
and b2.name = s1.bar
)
EXCEPT
(select distinct b1.name AS bar1, b2.name AS bar2, s1.beer AS beer
from bar AS b1, bar AS b2, serves as s1
where b1.name <> b2.name
and b1.name = s1.bar)) AS sub)
;

--(j) Find all (bar1, bar2) pairs where the set of beer served at bar1 is a proper subset of those served at bar2; i.e., bar2 serves every beer that bar1 serves and plus some more. 
(select s1.bar as bar1, s2.bar as bar2  -- (bar1, bar2) pairs where bar2 serves some beer that bar1 doesn't
 from serves as s1, serves as s2
 where not exists  -- s2.beer should be served at bar2 but not bar1
    (select * from serves as s3  -- Whether s1.bar serves s2.beer
     where s3.bar = s1.bar and s3.beer = s2.beer))
except
(select s1.bar as bar1, s2.bar as bar2  -- (bar1, bar2) pairs where bar1 serves some beer that bar2 doesn't
 from serves as s1, serves as s2
 where not exists  -- s1.beer should be served at bar1 but not bar2
    (select * from serves as s3  -- Whether s2.bar serves s1.beer
     where s3.bar = s2.bar and s3.beer = s1.beer));

-- Find all (bar1, bar2) pairs where the set of beer served at bar1
-- is a proper subset of those served at bar2.
-- i.e. bar2 serves every beer that bar1 serves, plus some more.



-- 1. Relation first (bar1, bar2):
-- Find all the bar1, bar2 pairs that are not the same 
-- in a theta join between servefirst and servesecond 
-- (serves cross serve). 

-- 2. Relation second (bar1, beer, bar2):  
-- Theta join of serves with itself, but you want to find where 
-- the beers are the same and the bars are not the same.

-- Collaborated with August Ning. 

SELECT sixth.bar1 AS bar1, sixth.bar2 AS bar2
FROM (
		SELECT * FROM (SELECT bar AS bar1 FROM serves) AS first, (SELECT bar AS bar2 FROM serves) AS second
		WHERE NOT first.bar1 = second.bar2

	EXCEPT

		(SELECT DISTINCT fifth.bar1, fifth.bar2
		FROM (SELECT DISTINCT first.bar1, first.beer, second.bar2
		FROM (SELECT bar AS bar1, beer FROM serves) AS first, (SELECT bar AS bar2 FROM serves) AS second WHERE NOT first.bar1 = second.bar2

	EXCEPT

		SELECT DISTINCT third.bar, third.beer, fourth.bar
		FROM (SELECT * FROM serves) AS third,
		(SELECT * FROM serves) AS fourth WHERE third.beer = fourth.beer AND NOT third.bar = fourth.bar) AS fifth) ) AS sixth

EXCEPT

SELECT sixth.bar2 AS bar1, sixth.bar1 AS bar2
FROM (
	SELECT * FROM (SELECT bar AS bar1 FROM serves) AS first, (SELECT bar AS bar2 FROM serves) AS second WHERE NOT first.bar1 = second.bar2

	EXCEPT

	(SELECT DISTINCT fifth.bar1, fifth.bar2 FROM (
	SELECT DISTINCT first.bar1, first.beer, second.bar2
	FROM (SELECT bar AS bar1, beer FROM serves) AS first, 
	(SELECT bar AS bar2 FROM serves) AS second WHERE NOT first.bar1 = second.bar2

	EXCEPT

	SELECT DISTINCT third.bar, third.beer, fourth.bar
	FROM (SELECT * FROM serves) AS third,
	(SELECT * FROM serves) AS fourth
	WHERE third.beer = fourth.beer AND NOT third.bar = fourth.bar) 
	AS fifth) 
) AS sixth
;

column1:
(SELECT b3.name, s3.bar 
FROM Bar b3 CROSS JOIN Serves s3 WHERE b3.name <> s3.bar)
EXCEPT (
	SELECT t.bar, t.name 
	FROM ((
		SELECT s2.bar, b2.name, s2.beer 
		FROM Bar b2 CROSS JOIN Serves s2 WHERE b2.name <> s2.bar) 
		EXCEPT (
			SELECT b1.name, s1.bar, s1.beer 
			FROM Bar b1 CROSS JOIN Serves s1 WHERE b1.name <> s1.bar)) AS t);

WITH join1(bar1, bar2, beer) 
	AS (SELECT serves.bar AS bar1, s1.bar AS bar2, s1.beer AS beer 
		FROM serves, serves AS s1 
		WHERE s1.bar <> serves.bar), 
join2(bar1,bar2,beer) 
	AS (SELECT s1.bar AS bar1, serves.bar AS bar2, s1.beer AS beer 
		FROM serves, serves AS s1 
		WHERE s1.bar <> serves.bar) 
SELECT bar1, bar2 FROM join1 
EXCEPT 
SELECT bar1, bar2 FROM 
	(SELECT * FROM join2 
	EXCEPT 
	SELECT * FROM join1) 
		AS joined;

SELECT DISTINCT bar2, bar1 from 

(


(SELECT rpairdiff1.bar2, rpairdiff1.bar1 FROM 
((SELECT pair.bar AS bar1, pair.beer AS beer, pair.name AS bar2
FROM (SELECT serves.bar, serves.beer, foo.name FROM serves CROSS JOIN (SELECT name FROM bar) as foo) as pair)

EXCEPT ALL

(SELECT rpair.name AS bar1, rpair.beer AS beer, rpair.bar AS bar2
FROM (SELECT serves.bar, serves.beer, foo.name FROM serves CROSS JOIN (SELECT name FROM bar) as foo) as rpair)
) AS rpairdiff1)


EXCEPT ALL



(SELECT bar1, bar2 from 

(SELECT rpairdiff1.bar2, rpairdiff1.bar1 FROM 
((SELECT pair.bar AS bar1, pair.beer AS beer, pair.name AS bar2
FROM (SELECT serves.bar, serves.beer, foo.name FROM serves CROSS JOIN (SELECT name FROM bar) as foo) as pair)

EXCEPT ALL

(SELECT rpair.name AS bar1, rpair.beer AS beer, rpair.bar AS bar2
FROM (SELECT serves.bar, serves.beer, foo.name FROM serves CROSS JOIN (SELECT name FROM bar) as foo) as rpair)
) AS rpairdiff1) as rdiff, 


(SELECT pairdiff2.bar3, pairdiff2.bar4 FROM

(SELECT helppairdiff2.bar1 AS bar3, helppairdiff2.beer AS beer, helppairdiff2.bar2 AS bar4 FROM
((SELECT pair.bar AS bar1, pair.beer AS beer, pair.name AS bar2
FROM (SELECT serves.bar, serves.beer, foo.name FROM serves CROSS JOIN (SELECT name FROM bar) as foo) as pair)

EXCEPT ALL

(SELECT rpair.name AS bar1, rpair.beer AS beer, rpair.bar AS bar2
FROM (SELECT serves.bar, serves.beer, foo.name FROM serves CROSS JOIN (SELECT name FROM bar) as foo) as rpair)) as helppairdiff2) as pairdiff2) as diff

WHERE

bar1= bar4 and bar3=bar2)) AS ans;

WITH bars(bar1, bar2) AS
(SELECT DISTINCT s1.bar, s2.bar
FROM serves s1, serves s2
WHERE s2.beer NOT IN
(SELECT DISTINCT beer
FROM serves
WHERE s1.bar = serves.bar)),
allbars(bar1, bar2) AS
(SELECT DISTINCT s1.bar, s2.bar
FROM serves s1, serves s2
WHERE s2.bar!=s1.bar),
subsets(bar1, bar2) AS
(SELECT *
FROM allbars
EXCEPT
SELECT *
FROM bars)
SELECT bar2, bar1
FROM subsets
EXCEPT
(SELECT b1.bar1, b1.bar2
FROM subsets b1, subsets b2
WHERE b1.bar1=b2.bar2 AND b1.bar2=b2.bar1);

WITH temp AS
(SELECT bar, array_agg(beer)
FROM Serves
GROUP BY bar)

SELECT temp1.bar, temp2.bar
FROM temp AS temp1, temp AS temp2
WHERE temp1.array_agg <@ temp2.array_agg
AND temp1.bar <> temp2.bar;

(SELECT Bar.name, Serves.Bar FROM Serves, Bar 
	WHERE NOT EXISTS 
	(SELECT Bar2.name, Serves2.beer, Serves2.bar FROM Bar Bar2, Serves Serves2 
		WHERE Bar2.name = Serves.bar 
		AND Serves2.beer = Serves.beer
		AND Serves2.bar = Bar.name))
EXCEPT
(SELECT Serves.bar, Bar.name FROM Serves, Bar 
	WHERE NOT EXISTS 
	(SELECT Bar2.name, Serves2.beer, Serves2.bar FROM Bar Bar2, Serves Serves2 
		WHERE Bar2.name = Serves.bar 
		AND Serves2.beer = Serves.beer
		AND Serves2.bar = Bar.name))

column1:
select bar1.bar bar1, bar2.bar bar2
from 
(
	select distinct bar, count(*) count
    from serves
    group by bar
)  bar1,
( 
	select distinct bar, count(*) count
    from serves
    group by bar
) bar2
where bar1.bar != bar2.bar
and bar1.count < bar2.count
and not exists 
(
	select beer
	from serves 
	where serves.bar = bar1.bar
	except
	select beer
	from   serves
	where serves.bar = bar2.bar
)

--e2
SELECT e2.name, e2.bar FROM
(SELECT Serves.bar, Serves.beer, Bar.name FROM --bar1, beer, bar2
Serves CROSS JOIN Bar --e1
  EXCEPT (
    SELECT Bar.name, Serves.beer, Serves.bar FROM
    Serves CROSS JOIN Bar
  )
)AS e2
EXCEPT (
  SELECT temp.bar, temp.name FROM
  (SELECT Serves.bar, Serves.beer, Bar.name FROM --bar1, beer, bar2
  Serves CROSS JOIN Bar --e1
    EXCEPT (
      SELECT Bar.name, Serves.beer, Serves.bar FROM
      Serves CROSS JOIN Bar
    )
  ) AS temp
)
;

SELECT d1.bar, d2.bar
FROM (
  SELECT bar, array_agg(beer), count(*)
  FROM serves
  GROUP BY bar
) AS d1,(
  SELECT bar, array_agg(beer), count(*)
  FROM serves
  GROUP BY bar
) AS d2
WHERE d1.array_agg <@ d2.array_agg
AND d1.count < d2.count;

(SELECT foo.bar2, foo.bar1
FROM (SELECT s1.bar AS bar1, s2.bar AS bar2, s1.beer
FROM serves AS s1, serves AS s2
WHERE s1.bar <> s2.bar

EXCEPT

SELECT s2.bar AS bar1, s1.bar AS bar2, s1.beer
FROM serves AS s1, serves AS s2
WHERE s1.bar <> s2.bar) AS foo)

EXCEPT

(SELECT foo.bar1, foo.bar2
FROM (SELECT DISTINCT s1.bar AS bar1, s2.bar AS bar2, s1.beer
FROM serves AS s1, serves AS s2
WHERE s1.bar <> s2.bar

EXCEPT

SELECT s2.bar AS bar1, s1.bar AS bar2, s1.beer
FROM serves AS s1, serves AS s2
WHERE s1.bar <> s2.bar) AS foo);

column1:
SELECT s1.bar AS bar1, s2.bar AS bar2
FROM Serves AS s1
CROSS JOIN Serves AS s2
WHERE s1.bar != s2.bar

EXCEPT

(
    /* A serves beer b doesn't serve*/
    SELECT bar1, bar2
    FROM (
        SELECT s3.bar AS bar1, 
        b1.name AS bar2, 
        s3.beer
        FROM Serves AS s3
        CROSS JOIN Bar AS b1

        EXCEPT

        SELECT b2.name AS bar1, 
        s4.bar AS bar2, 
        s4.beer
        FROM Serves AS s4
        CROSS JOIN Bar AS b2
    ) AS T1

    UNION

    /* b serves beer a doesn't serve */
    SELECT bar2 AS bar1, bar2 AS bar1
    FROM (
        SELECT b3.name AS bar1, 
        s5.bar AS bar2,
        s5.beer
        FROM Serves AS s5
        CROSS JOIN Bar AS b3

        EXCEPT

        SELECT s6.bar AS bar1, 
        b4.name AS bar2, 
        s6.beer
        FROM Serves AS s6
        CROSS JOIN Bar AS b4
    ) AS T2
);

/*bar with an array of its beers*/
WITH bcb as (
    SELECT bar, array_agg(beer) as beers
    FROM serves
    GROUP BY bar)
SELECT less.bar, more.bar
FROM  bcb as less CROSS JOIN bcb as more
WHERE less.beers <@ more.beers AND less.bar != more.bar;

column1:
SELECT b1.name, b2.name FROM Bar AS b1, Bar AS b2
WHERE NOT EXISTS
	(SELECT * FROM Serves
	WHERE bar = b1.name AND beer NOT IN
		(SELECT beer FROM Serves
		WHERE bar = b2.name))
AND EXISTS
	(SELECT * FROM Serves
	WHERE bar = b2.name AND beer NOT IN
		(SELECT beer FROM Serves
		WHERE bar = b1.name));

FROM	(SELECT bar1, bar2
		FROM	((SELECT T1.bar AS bar1, T1.beer AS beer, T2.bar AS bar2
				FROM (SELECT bar, beer FROM serves) AS T1,
				     (SELECT bar FROM serves) AS T2)

				EXCEPT

				(SELECT bar2 AS bar1, beer, bar1 AS bar2
				FROM (SELECT T11.bar AS bar1, T11.beer AS beer, T22.bar AS bar2
					 FROM (SELECT bar, beer FROM serves) AS T11,
					      (SELECT bar FROM serves) AS T22) AS T33)) AS T44) as T55)

			      (SELECT bar FROM serves) AS T2222) AS T3333)) AS T4444);

/* 
Find all (bar1, bar2) pairs where the set of beer served at bar1 is a proper subset of those served at bar2.
Can you find (bar1, bar2) pairs where there is some beer served at bar1 not served at bar2? 
*/

WITH subset AS (
    SELECT b1.name AS bar1, b2.name AS bar2
    FROM bar AS b1, bar AS b2
    WHERE b1.name <> b2.name
    AND NOT EXISTS (
        SELECT DISTINCT s1.bar, s2.bar
        FROM serves AS s1, serves AS s2
        WHERE s1.bar <> s2.bar
        AND 
        s1.beer NOT IN (
            SELECT beer
            FROM serves
            WHERE serves.bar = s2.bar
        )
        AND b1.name = s1.bar
        AND b2.name = s2.bar
    )
)
SELECT t1.bar1, t1.bar2
FROM subset AS t1
WHERE NOT EXISTS (
    SELECT *
    FROM subset AS t2
    WHERE t2.bar1 = t1.bar2 AND t2.bar2 = t1.bar1
);

with  combinations(bar1,beer, bar2)  as
(select serves.bar, serves.beer, bar.name from serves, bar),

theSwap(bar2, beer, bar1) as
(select bar2, beer,bar1 from combinations),

theDiff (barA,beer, barB) as
((select * from combinations) except (select * from theSwap)),

mySw(barB,beer,barA) as
(select barB, beer, barA from theDiff)

(select barB, barA from mySw) except
(select T1.bar1, T1.bar2 from (select barB as bar1, barA as bar2 from mySw)  as T1, (select barB as bar3, barA as bar4 from mySw) as T2 where bar1= bar4 and bar2= bar3);

WITH increasingBars AS
(SELECT bar, COUNT(beer) FROM serves GROUP BY bar),

candidatePairs AS
(SELECT i1.bar AS bar1, i2.bar AS bar2, COUNT(*) AS count FROM increasingBars AS i1, increasingBars AS i2, serves as s WHERE i1.count < i2.count AND s.bar = i1.bar GROUP BY bar1, bar2),

mutualBeers AS
(SELECT s1.bar AS bar1, s2.bar AS bar2, COUNT(*) AS count FROM serves AS s1, serves AS s2 WHERE s1.beer = s2.beer GROUP BY bar1, bar2),

candidates AS
((SELECT bar1, bar2, count FROM candidatePairs) INTERSECT (SELECT bar1, bar2, count FROM mutualBeers))

SELECT bar1, bar2 FROM candidates;

WITH Y AS
(
  SELECT X.bar1, X.beer, X.bar2
  FROM
  (
    SELECT bar.name as bar1, bar.address, serves.bar as bar2, serves.beer, serves.price
    FROM bar, serves
  ) X
  EXCEPT
  SELECT X2.bar2, X2.beer, X2.bar1
  FROM
  (
    SELECT bar.name as bar1, bar.address, serves.bar as bar2, serves.beer, serves.price
    FROM bar, serves
  ) X2
)
SELECT Y.bar1, Y.bar2
FROM Y
EXCEPT
SELECT Y2.bar2, Y2.bar1
FROM Y as Y2;

column1:
--Find all bar1 bar2 pairs where bar2 serves something bar1 doesn't
--This doesn't include bar1 bar2 pairs where bar1 serves nothing
((SELECT DISTINCT S1.bar, S2.bar
FROM Serves AS S1, Serves AS S2
WHERE S1.bar!=S2.bar
AND S2.beer NOT IN (SELECT beer
					FROM Serves
					WHERE S1.bar=bar))
--Remove bar1 bar2 pairs where bar1 serves something bar2 doesn't
EXCEPT
(SELECT DISTINCT S1.bar, S2.bar
FROM Serves AS S1, Serves AS S2
WHERE S1.bar!=S2.bar
AND S1.beer NOT IN (SELECT beer
					FROM Serves
					WHERE S2.bar=bar)))
--Add bar1 bar2 pairs where bar1 serves nothing but bar2 serves something
UNION
(SELECT DISTINCT name, bar
FROM Bar, Serves
WHERE name NOT IN (SELECT bar
					FROM Serves)
AND bar IN (SELECT bar
			FROM Serves));

  FROM (SELECT bar, beer FROM serves) barbeer, (SELECT name FROM bar) barbeer2

(SELECT bar1, bar2 FROM temp2);

--Find all (bar1, bar2) pairs where the set of beer served at bar1 is a proper subset of those served at
--bar2; i.e., bar2 serves every beer that bar1 serves and plus some more
-- (\project_{bar2, bar}(
-- temp1 (\project_{bar, bar2, beer} (serves \join_{bar <> bar2} (\rename_{bar2, address} bar)))
-- temp3 \diff
-- temp2 (\project_{bar2, bar, beer} ((\rename_{bar2, address} bar) \join_{bar <> bar2} serves))))

-- \diff(
--oppposite
-- bar2, bar pair
-- bar, bar2, beer serves join bar where the bars are not equal (makes bar, bar2) diff this from the 
-- bar2, bar, beer bar join serves where bars are not equal (makes bar2, bar pairs)

-- diff that entire thing with the same as 29/30 lines but do bar, bar2

-- -make a view that is 

WITH temp1 (bar1, bar2, beer) AS (
SELECT DISTINCT serves.bar, bar.name, serves.beer
FROM serves, bar
WHERE serves.bar != bar.name),

temp2(bar2, bar1, beer) AS (
SELECT DISTINCT bar.name, serves.bar, serves.beer
FROM bar, serves
WHERE bar.name!= serves.bar
),

temp3 (bar1, bar2) AS(
SELECT bar1, bar2, beer
FROM temp1 
EXCEPT 
SELECT bar2, bar1, beer
FROM temp2),


temp4(bar2, bar1) AS(
SELECT bar2, bar1, beer
FROM temp1
EXCEPT
SELECT bar1, bar2, beer
FROM temp2)


SELECT bar2, bar1
FROM temp3

EXCEPT

SELECT bar1, bar2
FROM temp4;

/*Find all (bar1, bar2) pairs where the set of beer served at bar1 is a proper subset of those served at
bar2; i.e., bar2 serves every beer that bar1 serves and plus some more. */ 

SELECT final.name, final.bar FROM(
(SELECT sub.name, sub.bar FROM(
(SELECT serves.bar, beer, bar.name FROM serves, bar)
EXCEPT
(SELECT bar.name, beer, serves.bar FROM serves, bar))sub)
EXCEPT
(SELECT sub1.bar, sub1.name FROM(
(SELECT serves.bar, beer, bar.name FROM serves, bar)
EXCEPT
(SELECT bar.name, beer, serves.bar FROM serves, bar))sub1))final;

WITH
tmp1(bar1, beer1, price1) AS
(SELECT * FROM Serves),

tmp2(bar2, beer2, price2) AS
(SELECT * FROM Serves),

tmp3(bar1,bar2, beer2) AS
(SELECT bar1, bar2, beer2 FROM (tmp1 JOIN tmp2 ON tmp1.bar1<>tmp2.bar2)),

tmp4(bar1,bar2, beer1) AS
(SELECT bar1, bar2, beer1 FROM (tmp1 JOIN tmp2 ON tmp1.bar1<>tmp2.bar2)),

tmp5(bar1, bar2, beer2) AS
(SELECT * FROM tmp3 EXCEPT SELECT * FROM tmp4),

tmp6(bar1, bar2) AS
(SELECT bar1, bar2 FROM tmp5),

tmp7(bar1, bar2, beer1) AS
(SELECT * FROM tmp4 EXCEPT SELECT * FROM tmp3),

tmp8(bar1, bar2) AS
(SELECT bar1, bar2 FROM tmp7),

tmp9(bar1) AS
(SELECT * FROM tmp6 EXCEPT SELECT * FROM tmp8)

SELECT * FROM tmp9;

SELECT DISTINCT s2.bar, s1.bar
FROM serves AS s1, serves as s2
WHERE s1.bar != s2.bar AND
EXISTS (
	SELECT beer
	FROM serves AS s3
	WHERE s3.bar = s1.bar

	EXCEPT

	SELECT beer
	FROM serves AS s4
	WHERE s4.bar = s2.bar
) 
AND
NOT EXISTS (
	SELECT beer
	FROM serves AS s4
	WHERE s4.bar = s2.bar

	EXCEPT

	SELECT beer
	FROM serves AS s3
	WHERE s3.bar = s1.bar
);

WITH Y AS
(SELECT X.bar1, X.beer, X.bar2
  FROM
  (SELECT bar.name as bar1, bar.address, serves.bar as bar2, serves.beer, serves.price
    FROM bar, serves) X
  EXCEPT
  SELECT X2.bar2, X2.beer, X2.bar1
  FROM
  (SELECT bar.name as bar1, bar.address, serves.bar as bar2, serves.beer, serves.price
    FROM bar, serves
  ) X2)
SELECT Y.bar1, Y.bar2
FROM Y EXCEPT
  SELECT Y2.bar2, Y2.bar1
  FROM Y as Y2;

WITH Bar_beer_count AS
(SELECT bar, COUNT(*) AS count
FROM Serves
GROUP BY bar)
SELECT DISTINCT bar1.name AS bar1, bar2.name AS bar2
FROM Bar AS bar1, Bar AS bar2
WHERE bar1.name != bar2.name
EXCEPT
SELECT DISTINCT bar1.bar AS bar1, bar2.bar AS bar2
FROM serves AS bar1, serves AS bar2
WHERE bar1.beer NOT IN
(SELECT beer
FROM serves
WHERE serves.bar = bar2.bar)
EXCEPT
SELECT c1.bar, c2.bar
FROM Bar_beer_count AS c1, Bar_beer_count AS c2
WHERE c1.bar != c2.bar
AND c1.count = c2.count;

SELECT DISTINCT bars1.name AS bar1, bars2.name as bar2
FROM (SELECT name FROM bar) AS bars1 JOIN (SELECT name FROM bar) AS bars2 ON
  -- For all pairs of bars
  bars1.name <> bars2.name
WHERE NOT exists (
  -- There doesn't exist a beer served by bar1 but not served by bar2
  SELECT beer from serves WHERE bar = bars1.name
  EXCEPT (
    SELECT beer from serves WHERE bar = bars2.name
  )
) AND exists(
  -- And there exists beer(s) served by bar2 but not served by bar1
  SELECT beer from serves WHERE bar = bars2.name
  EXCEPT (
    SELECT beer from serves WHERE bar = bars1.name
  )
);
